pdfocr adds an OCR text layer to scanned PDF files, allowing them to be searched. It currently depends on Ruby 1.8.7 or above, and relies on cuneiform for performing OCR.

To use, run:

pdfocr -i input.pdf -o output.pdf

For more details, see the manpage.

pdfocr was written by Geza Kovacs

pdfocr is hosted at http://github.com/gkovacs/pdfocr
